<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-25T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-25T14:00:00-05:00" n="546" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d546">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/5501:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-25T14:00:00-05:00">October 25, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>637. Department’s 636, October 25, noon. In view of the uncertainty
                                that the President’s message as communicated to you was accurately
                                delivered to Marshal Pétain, please obtain at the first possible
                                moment an audience with the Marshal and repeat to him the contents
                                of the President’s message.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>